## Phase 4: Model Drift Detection

### Three types of drift to monitor:

#### Data Drift (Input Distribution Shifts)
- Track per-frame: mean brightness, contrast, color histogram
- Metric: **Population Stability Index (PSI)**
  - PSI < 0.1 → No drift
  - 0.1 < PSI < 0.2 → Moderate drift (investigate)
  - PSI > 0.2 → Significant drift (alert, consider retraining)
- Example trigger: *"Average brightness dropped 40% after daylight savings — night frames now dominate"*

#### Prediction Drift (Output Distribution Shifts)
- Track per-hour: mean confidence, detection count per frame, class distribution ratios
- Metric: **Kolmogorov-Smirnov test** on rolling windows
- Example trigger: *"Bus detections dropped 60% since last Tuesday — possible model degradation or route change"*

#### Concept Drift (Input-Output Relationship Changes)
- Track: correlation between brightness and confidence (should be stable)
- If correlation coefficient shifts > 2σ from baseline → concept drift
- Example trigger: *"Model's confidence no longer correlates with image quality — the model may have degraded"*

### Drift monitoring outputs:
- `drift_metrics.jsonl` — time-series log of all metrics
- Color-coded CLI dashboard (green/yellow/red per metric)
- Time-series plots saved to `docs/drift_reports/`
- Root cause suggestions: *"Drift detected 18:00-19:00 daily — correlates with sunset transition. Consider time-aware model switching."*

